# File Structure Guidelines

## Directory Organization

### Component Structure
```
components/
├── Button/
│   ├── Button.tsx          # Component implementation
│   ├── Button.test.tsx     # Component tests
│   ├── Button.stories.tsx  # Storybook stories
│   └── index.ts            # Public exports
├── Card/
│   ├── Card.tsx
│   ├── Card.test.tsx
│   └── index.ts
└── index.ts                # Barrel export
```

### Feature-Based Structure
```
features/
├── auth/
│   ├── components/
│   ├── hooks/
│   ├── services/
│   ├── types/
│   └── index.ts
├── dashboard/
│   ├── components/
│   ├── hooks/
│   └── index.ts
└── index.ts
```

## File Naming

### Components
```typescript
// ✅ Good: PascalCase for component files
UserProfile.tsx
NavigationMenu.tsx
Button.tsx

// ❌ Bad: camelCase or kebab-case
userProfile.tsx
navigation-menu.tsx
```

### Utilities and Hooks
```typescript
// ✅ Good: camelCase for utilities and hooks
formatDate.ts
useAuth.ts
calculateTotal.ts

// ✅ Good: kebab-case for config files
eslint.config.js
tsconfig.json
```

### Test Files
```typescript
// ✅ Good: Consistent test file naming
Button.test.tsx
Button.spec.tsx
__tests__/Button.test.tsx

// Match the source file name
```

## File Organization

### Single Responsibility
```typescript
// ✅ Good: One component per file
// Button.tsx
export function Button() { }

// ❌ Bad: Multiple components in one file
// Buttons.tsx
export function Button() { }
export function IconButton() { }
export function LinkButton() { }
```

### Barrel Exports
```typescript
// ✅ Good: index.ts for clean imports
// components/index.ts
export { Button } from './Button';
export { Card } from './Card';
export { Input } from './Input';

// Usage
import { Button, Card, Input } from '@/components';
```

## Import Organization

### Import Order
1. React and React-related imports
2. Third-party libraries
3. Internal absolute imports (@/...)
4. Relative imports
5. Type imports
6. CSS/asset imports

```typescript
// ✅ Good: Organized imports
import React, { useState, useEffect } from 'react';
import { useRouter } from 'next/router';
import { Button } from '@/components/Button';
import { UserService } from '@/services/UserService';
import type { User } from '@/types/User';
import './styles.css';
```

## Configuration Files

### Placement
```
project-root/
├── .eslintrc.js           # ESLint config
├── .prettierrc            # Prettier config
├── tsconfig.json          # TypeScript config
├── jest.config.js         # Jest config
├── package.json           # Dependencies
└── .env.example           # Environment variables template
```

## Best Practices

1. **Group related files** - Keep related files together
2. **Use consistent naming** - Follow project conventions
3. **Keep files focused** - One responsibility per file
4. **Use barrel exports** - Simplify imports with index.ts
5. **Organize by feature** - Group by feature when appropriate
6. **Separate concerns** - Keep components, hooks, utils separate
